{"questionId":"13351180","questionHtml":"<p>Write down the null and alternative hypotheses for his test.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>≠</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>≠</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept an equivalent statement in words, but must include reference to “population mean” / “mean for class A and class B” for the <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>to be awarded.</p>\n<p>Do not accept an imprecise “<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">the means</span> are equal”.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13351180","referenceCode":"23N.1.SL.TZ2.9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathema